messages.message:
Anyone else seeing/has seen their cypress CI fail but not provide a URL or any list of failed tests? Seems like the job isn’t correctly picking up the test results
https://github.com/instabase/instabase/actions/runs/11446149265/job/31846569280?pr=63978
Seems like `aihub-custom-function-field.spec.ts` is failing consistently due to extraction failure cc <!subteam^S07855GV3GV>
I need to rotate <!subteam^S07855GV3GV> as well

Also, perhaps the runs aren’t being printed out because the runs are apparently canceled according to cloud.cypress.io (http://cloud.cypress.io)? I’m actually not too sure myself why they’re not appearing.

Hmm, looking deeper, it may be because our test suite takes too long to run? We’re getting a `This socket has been ended by the other party` error in the middle of our test (see screenshot). But it failed after 35 minutes which seems too short for a timeout.

https://github.com/instabase/instabase/actions/runs/11449312455/job/31855044386?pr=64103

Seems like it’s actually a crash on Cypress’ end and we need to upgrade to `13.10.0` : https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress/issues/27552
https://github.com/cypress-io/cypress/pull/29499
I’ll put up a PR.
